## Error Shape (standard)
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "Human-readable message",
    "details": {}
  }
}
```

## Status Codes
| Code | Meaning | When |
|------|---------|------|
| 200 | OK | Successful read/update |
| 201 | Created | Successful creation |
| 400 | Bad Request | Validation failure |
| 401 | Unauthorized | Missing/invalid auth |
| 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |
| 404 | Not Found | Resource doesn't exist |
| 500 | Internal Error | Unexpected server error |

## Versioning Policy
- API changes must be additive (new fields, new endpoints).
- Removals or type changes require /core escalation and a migration plan.
- Breaking changes must update this document BEFORE implementation.
